MOUNTAIN VIEW, CA -- November 4, 2009 -- YippieMove, the leader in cloud-based email migration, today introduces a new tool to migrate multiple email accounts simultaneously. The new tool is named Batch Control Panel (BCP) and works with any IMAP compatible server.<br/>Batch Control Panel features the same reliable back-end as the single-transfer tool available at YippieMove.com that caters to consumers.<br/><!--more--><br/><strong>A  simple three step process</strong><br/>Email migration with Batch Control Panel is a simple three step process:<br/><ol><br/>	<li>Download a CSV template.</li><br/>	<li>Fill out the CSV file with information about the source and destination accounts.</li><br/>	<li>Upload the file into Batch Control Panel and press start.</li><br/></ol><br/>Once the transfer has started, near-realtime statistics of the transfer are generated to provide effective monitoring of the transfers.<br/>YippieMove and YippieMove Batch Control Panel can be used with most email servers on the market, including Courier-IMAP, Cyrus, Lotus iNotes, Microsoft Exchange and Zimbra.<br/>YippieMove Batch Control Panel was designed for consultants, ISPs and IT professionals looking for a simple way to provide email migration for their clients. Since no downloads are required and transfers are performed directly on high-speed servers, YippieMove is the natural choice for hassle-free email migration.<br/>The migrations are priced at $14.95 per account, with volume discounts available.<br/><h3>Screenshots</h3><br/>[caption id="attachment_197" align="aligncenter" width="300" caption="Add a new batch"]<a href="http://wireload.net/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/bcp_add_batch.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-197" title="Add a new batch" src="http://wireload.net/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/bcp_add_batch-300x230.png" alt="Add a new batch" width="300" height="230" /></a>[/caption]<br/>[caption id="attachment_198" align="aligncenter" width="300" caption="A new batch is ready"]<a href=